00:05:57.050 --> 00:05:58.790
What's the bottom line?

00:05:58.790 --> 00:06:02.790
With all of this computing,
going golf ball to sun,

00:06:02.790 --> 00:06:04.410
we're increasingly connected.

00:06:04.410 --> 00:06:07.750
We're dependent upon these
systems, and we're vulnerable.

00:06:07.750 --> 00:06:09.810
Computers run all our
critical infrastructures,

00:06:09.810 --> 00:06:13.130
from electricity to
health care to 911 system.

00:06:13.130 --> 00:06:14.752
And they're all hackable.

00:06:14.752 --> 00:06:16.210
There's never been
built a computer

00:06:16.210 --> 00:06:17.501
system that couldn't be hacked.

00:06:17.501 --> 00:06:20.730
And we keep rushing, connecting
more and more stuff to the net,

00:06:20.730 --> 00:06:22.990
but more connections
equals more vulnerability.

00:06:22.990 --> 00:06:24.510
So what do we do?

00:06:24.510 --> 00:06:26.840
I'm not saying
technology is bad, right?

00:06:26.840 --> 00:06:27.880
I'm in Silicon Valley.

00:06:27.880 --> 00:06:28.790
I love tech.

00:06:28.790 --> 00:06:29.680
Tech is awesome.

00:06:29.680 --> 00:06:31.780
Fire was the first technology.

00:06:31.780 --> 00:06:33.480
It could keep you warm at night.

00:06:33.480 --> 00:06:35.800
It could cook food
in your cave, or you

00:06:35.800 --> 00:06:38.420
could use it to burn down
the village next to yours.

00:06:38.420 --> 00:06:40.050
It's just how we're using it.

00:06:40.050 --> 00:06:42.090
But make no mistake,
there is a war afoot

00:06:42.090 --> 00:06:44.450
between people that want
to use tech for good

00:06:44.450 --> 00:06:46.600
and people that want
to use tech for evil.

00:06:46.600 --> 00:06:49.760
And in exponential times,
the ability of one person

00:06:49.760 --> 00:06:52.710
to reach out to 100
million or a billion people

00:06:52.710 --> 00:06:54.230
is a growing problem
that we haven't

00:06:54.230 --> 00:06:56.730
solved how to handle yet.

00:06:56.730 --> 00:06:59.200
When the entire world
is becoming a computer,

00:06:59.200 --> 00:07:02.430
Marc Andreessen famously said
software is eating the world.

00:07:02.430 --> 00:07:06.670
When maps become GPS
devices, when music becomes

00:07:06.670 --> 00:07:08.750
Spotify and Netflix is movies.

00:07:08.750 --> 00:07:10.910
Every physical object
is becoming a computer.

00:07:10.910 --> 00:07:12.600
And all computers
are run by code.

00:07:12.600 --> 00:07:15.640
So if you can control the
code, in a world where

00:07:15.640 --> 00:07:18.940
computers run the world, then
you can control the world.

00:07:18.940 --> 00:07:21.370
And the biggest problem
is, unlike other times,

00:07:21.370 --> 00:07:23.800
most people have no idea
that they're a victim.

00:07:23.800 --> 00:07:26.430
If you go out your garage in the
morning and look for your car

00:07:26.430 --> 00:07:29.230
and it's missing, you're like,
holy cow, my car was stolen.

00:07:29.230 --> 00:07:32.180
But when bad guys break into
your computer, you don't know.

00:07:32.180 --> 00:07:35.710
According to a study by the
US Secret Service and Verizon,

00:07:35.710 --> 00:07:38.270
only 6% of hacks
of data breaches

00:07:38.270 --> 00:07:40.720
are picked up by the
system administrator.

00:07:40.720 --> 00:07:43.500
94% of the time, it's
because customers complain,

00:07:43.500 --> 00:07:45.270
the FBI comes knocking
at their door,

00:07:45.270 --> 00:07:47.510
or a competitor was also hacked.

00:07:47.510 --> 00:07:49.690
And this is a really
scary statistic.

00:07:49.690 --> 00:07:51.540
This is the time to discovery.

00:07:51.540 --> 00:07:56.640
On average, it takes an American
Fortune 500 company 211 days

00:07:56.640 --> 00:07:57.985
to know that they're penetrated.

00:07:57.985 --> 00:07:59.360
Which means that
the bad guys are

00:07:59.360 --> 00:08:01.830
living in your system
for nearly seven months,

00:08:01.830 --> 00:08:03.500
roaming around,
putting in back doors,

00:08:03.500 --> 00:08:05.380
leaving malware,
watching and studying

00:08:05.380 --> 00:08:07.240
everything that you're doing.

00:08:07.240 --> 00:08:09.590
And in the same study,
they said that 75%

00:08:09.590 --> 00:08:11.490
of American
corporations networks

00:08:11.490 --> 00:08:14.780
could be penetrated
in just 15 minutes.

00:08:14.780 --> 00:08:18.170
So breaking into the information
technologies of today

00:08:18.170 --> 00:08:20.360
is a lot like a hot knife
going through butter.

00:08:20.360 --> 00:08:21.480
It's super easy.

00:08:21.480 --> 00:08:24.370
And yet all of these
computers are the foundations

00:08:24.370 --> 00:08:25.700
of our modern world.

00:08:25.700 --> 00:08:27.520
So when they fail,
when they're hacked,

00:08:27.520 --> 00:08:30.390
when that cyber crisis occurs,
what is our backup plan?

00:08:30.390 --> 00:08:31.610
We don't have one.

00:08:31.610 --> 00:08:34.240
In effect, our modern
society's is kind of

00:08:34.240 --> 00:08:36.480
built on a digital
house of cards

00:08:36.480 --> 00:08:39.360
that can come falling down
unless we start to care for.

00:08:39.360 --> 00:08:41.309
This is how we handle
cyber threats today.

00:08:41.309 --> 00:08:42.580
We arrest people.

00:08:42.580 --> 00:08:46.070
The problem is that NYPD officer
cannot make an address right,

00:08:46.070 --> 00:08:49.010
in Moscow, or in Canada.

00:08:49.010 --> 00:08:50.190
Internet broke policing.

00:08:50.190 --> 00:08:53.880
Policing only works city to
city, country to country.

00:08:53.880 --> 00:08:56.100
International law is
horrible for these types

00:08:56.100 --> 00:08:58.290
of investigations,
and therefore we

00:08:58.290 --> 00:09:01.840
will never investigate or arrest
our way out of the cyber threat

00:09:01.840 --> 00:09:02.380
problem.

00:09:02.380 --> 00:09:04.390
The two systems are
completely mismatched,

00:09:04.390 --> 00:09:07.300
and yet this is the
primary tool we use today.

00:09:07.300 --> 00:09:08.886
Right, the cops,
we're in charge.

00:09:08.886 --> 00:09:10.010
We're going to handle this.

00:09:10.010 --> 00:09:11.970
We need to break that
paradigm of policing.

00:09:11.970 --> 00:09:13.750
We need to get the
public involved.

